abstract: BOSTON, Nov. 28. -- Three Deer Island prisoners had a narrow escape from drowning off Winthrop last night. Shortly before 6 o'clock "Block" Adams, "Boxer" Lyons, two-year men, and a colored prisoner under sentence of three months, made a hasty retreat from the island. The trio got other prisoners to engage the attention of the guards while the men were about to line up for their march to their quarters.
